# Quickstart

Get from zero to a running site in a few minutes.

## Requirements

Before installing Marque, make sure you have:

- Node.js 18 or newer
- npm (comes with Node.js)

Check your versions:

```bash
node -v
npm -v
````

## Installation

### Install from source (recommended)

Clone the repository and install dependencies:

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd marque
npm install
npm link
```

This makes the `marque` command available globally.

### Verify installation

```bash
marque --help
```

If the command runs, you're ready to go.

## Create and run your site

@steps quickstart
@step
## Create a project
Scaffold a new site:

````
```bash
marque new my-site
cd my-site
```
````

@end step

@step
## Start the dev server
Run the local server with live reload:

````
```bash
marque serve .
```

Then open http://localhost:3000
````

@end step

@step
## Edit content
Modify files inside `pages/`.
Changes are reflected instantly in your browser.
@end step

@step
## Build for production
Generate static files:

````
```bash
marque build .
```

Output is written to `dist/`.
````

@end step
@end steps quickstart

@row commands
@card .ghost
## Core commands

````
```bash
marque new my-site
marque serve .
marque build .
```
````

@end card

@card
## Project structure

````
```text
my-site/
├── pages/      # .mq content
├── static/     # copied as-is
├── marque.toml # config
└── dist/       # build output
```
````

@end card
@end row commands

